## Implementation Plan

### Goal
Replace all SENTRY_RELEASE_BOT variable/secret references with SENTRY_INTERNAL_APP,
which has the necessary permissions on this repo for auto-approve functionality.

### Changes Made

#### .github/workflows/auto-approve.yml
- Actor check: Added getsantry[bot] alongside sentry-release-bot[bot] (OR condition)
- vars.SENTRY_RELEASE_BOT_CLIENT_ID → vars.SENTRY_INTERNAL_APP_ID
- secrets.SENTRY_RELEASE_BOT_PRIVATE_KEY → secrets.SENTRY_INTERNAL_APP_PRIVATE_KEY

#### .github/workflows/publish.yml
- Step name: "Get Release Bot auth token" → "Get auth token"
- vars.SENTRY_RELEASE_BOT_CLIENT_ID → vars.SENTRY_INTERNAL_APP_ID
- secrets.SENTRY_RELEASE_BOT_PRIVATE_KEY → secrets.SENTRY_INTERNAL_APP_PRIVATE_KEY
- Comment: "Release Bot App" → "Internal App"

#### README.md
- Updated variable name references in prose to SENTRY_INTERNAL_APP_ID / SENTRY_INTERNAL_APP_PRIVATE_KEY
- Updated "Sentry Release Bot" → "the Sentry Internal App" in action-prepare-release context

### Preserved (intentionally not changed)
- sentry-release-bot[bot] actor name kept in the OR condition (larger migration needed)
- [Sentry Release Bot](https://github.com/apps/sentry-release-bot) link in README preserved

### Prerequisites
- Org-level variable SENTRY_INTERNAL_APP_ID and secret SENTRY_INTERNAL_APP_PRIVATE_KEY
  are already configured.
- The internal app actor name is getsantry[bot] (GitHub App slug: getsantry).
